-- Czech Inspectors Find Horse DNA in Meatballs for Ikea Stores
-- B y   P e t e r   L a c a
-- 2013-02-25T10:51:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-25/czech-inspectors-find-horse-dna-in-meatballs-for-ikea-stores.html
Czech inspectors found undeclared
traces of horse DNA in meatballs destined for outlets of the
Swedish furniture maker and retailer Ikea Group, the State
Veterinary Office said.  The meatballs were produced in Sweden, spokesman Josef
Duben said in an e-mailed statement from Prague today. Ikea
officials in Sweden did not immediately comment when contacted
by  Bloomberg News .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Peter Laca in Prague at 
